subject: resource/Sinclair_Vehicles
object: Sinclair Vehicles Ltd was a company formed in March 1983 by Sir Clive Sinclair as a focus for his work in the field of electric vehicles. The initial investment was £8.6m, which came from the proceeds of the sale of some of Sir Clive's shares in Sinclair Research. Barrie Wills, formerly of the DeLorean Motor Company, was appointed as managing director.The first (and only) Sinclair Vehicles production model was the single-seater Sinclair C5, launched on 10 January 1985.
